events.name: Notre Dame Fighting Irish at USC Trojans

headlines.description: Theo Riddick rushed for 146 yards and a touchdown, Kyle Brindza kicked five field goals, and No. 1 Notre Dame secured a spot in the BCS championship game with a 22-13 victory over Southern California on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irish handle USC to earn title shot

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: AJ McCarron passed for four touchdowns and Eddie Lacy rushed for 131 yards and two scores to lead the Crimson Tide to a 49-0 beatdown of rival Auburn on Saturday in the most lopsided Iron Bowl in 64 years.

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Aaron Murray threw two touchdown passes, Todd Gurley and Keith Marshall each ran for a pair of TDs, and No. 3 Georgia stayed right in the thick of the national championship race with a 42-10 rout of Georgia Tech on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia rolls before SEC title game

events.name: Florida Gators at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Mike Gillislee ran for two touchdowns and Florida (No. 4 BCS, No. 6 AP) scored 24 straight points in the fourth quarter to defeat No. 10 Florida State 37-26 Saturday and keep its national title hopes alive.

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: Kenjon Barner ran for 198 yards and two touchdowns despite leaving the game for a time with an injury and No. 5 Oregon defeated No. 16 Oregon State 48-24 in the Civil War on Saturday, keeping alive the Ducks' hopes for a spot in the Pac-12 title game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oregon bounces back, flattens Oregon State

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Stepfan Taylor rushed for 142 yards and two touchdowns, Kevin Hogan passed for 160 yards and another score, and Stanford (No. 8 BCS, No. 11 AP) beat UCLA (No. 17, No. 15) 35-17 Saturday to win the Pacific-12 Conference North title.

events.name: Missouri Tigers at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Johnny Manziel threw for 372 yards and three touchdowns and ran for two more scores as No. 9 Texas A&M beat Missouri 59-29 on Saturday night.

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Backup quarterback Dylan Thompson threw for three touchdowns, Jadeveon Clowney had 4½ sacks and South Carolina (No. 12 BCS, No. 13 AP) won its fourth straight over Clemson (No. 11, No. 12) 27-17 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurrier sets mark as S. Carolina tops Clemson

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Landry Jones threw for 500 yards and three touchdowns, and Brennan Clay scored on an 18-yard run in overtime to lift Oklahoma to a 51-48 win against Oklahoma State in the Bedlam rivalry on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones leads Sooners to Bedlam win

events.name: Rutgers Scarlet Knights at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: Tino Sunseri passed for 227 yards and two touchdowns in his final home game as Pittsburgh overwhelmed Rutgers (No. 18 BCS, No. 21 AP) 27-6 on Saturday.

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Carlos Hyde ran for 146 yards and Ohio State's (No. 4 AP) defense shut out Michigan (No. 19 BCS, No. 20 AP) in the second half to grab a bruising 26-21 victory on Saturday, completing an improbable 12-0 season for the Buckeyes.

events.name: Connecticut Huskies at Louisville Cardinals

headlines.description: Chad Christen's 30-yard field goal in the third overtime gave Connecticut a 23-20 upset of Louisville (No. 20 BCS, No. 19 AP) on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Louisville loses in OT, stays alive for BCS bowl

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Venric Mark rushed for 127 yards and a touchdown as Northwestern improved its chances for a berth in a New Year's Day bowl game, beating Illinois 50-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: N'western ups bowl chances with Illinois romp

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Cody Journell kicked a 29-yard field goal with 4 seconds to play, and Virginia Tech beat Virginia 17-14 Saturday to qualify for a bowl game and win its ninth straight from its in-state rival.
headlines.shortLinkText: Va. Tech edges Virginia, becomes bowl eligible

events.name: UAB Blazers at UCF Knights

headlines.description: UCF 49, UAB 24

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description: Akeem Shavers broke open a close game with three scores during a 4½-minute span in the fourth quarter, giving Purdue a 56-35 victory over archrival Indiana on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shavers key late as Purdue finishes off Indiana

events.name: Tulsa Golden Hurricane at SMU Mustangs

headlines.description: SMU 35, Tulsa 27

events.name: Kentucky Wildcats at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Tyler Bray threw four touchdown passes without an interception Saturday as Tennessee defeated Kentucky 37-17 in the season finale for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bray tosses 4 TDs, leads Tenn. past Kentucky

events.name: Miami Hurricanes at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: Freshman Duke Johnson rushed for season highs of 176 yards and three touchdowns, Stephen Morris had three passing scores and Miami held on to beat Duke 52-45 on Saturday and claim a share of the ACC's Coastal Division title.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miami clinches share of ACC Coastal Division

events.name: North Texas Mean Green at Western Kentucky Hilltoppers

headlines.description: W. Kentucky 25, North Texas 24

events.name: Coastal Carolina Chanticleers at Bethune-Cookman Wildcats

notes.headline: NCAA DIVISION I FOOTBALL CHAMPIONSHIP - FIRST ROUND

headlines.description: Coastal Carolina 24, Bethune-Cookman 14

events.name: Texas State Bobcats at UT San Antonio Roadrunners
Baylor Bears at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Glasco Martin scored on a 4-yard run in overtime and Baylor overcame three missed field goals, including one on the last play of regulation, to become bowl eligible with a 52-45 victory over Texas Tech on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baylor bowl eligible after outlasting Texas Tech

events.name: Boston College Eagles at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description: Mike Glennon threw three touchdown passes and David Amerson returned an interception for a score Saturday as North Carolina State defeated Boston College 27-10 in the teams' regular-season finale.
headlines.shortLinkText: Glennon powers NC State past Boston College

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Bryn Renner tied a school record with five touchdown passes, while Gio Bernard ran for 163 yards and a score to help North Carolina beat Maryland 45-38 in the finale for both teams Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Renner's school-record 5 TD passes lead UNC

events.name: Idaho Vandals at Utah State Aggies

headlines.description: Chuckie Keeton passed for two touchdowns, Kerwynn Williams rushed for 110 yards and senior Will Davis returned an interception 59 yards for a touchdown as No. 25 Utah State beat Idaho on Saturday to secure its first outright conference title in 76 years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah St. routs Idaho to clinch outright WAC title

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: Le'Veon Bell rumbled for a career-high 266 yards and a fourth-quarter touchdown to put the game away, leading Michigan State to a 26-10 victory over Minnesota on Saturday to secure a spot in a bowl game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Michigan St. claims spot in bowl as Bell shines

events.name: Vanderbilt Commodores at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Jordan Rodgers threw for 229 yards and two touchdowns, and Zac Stacy ran for a season-high 180 yards and two scores as Vanderbilt defeated Wake Forest 55-21 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vanderbilt pounds Wake for sixth straight win

events.name: BYU Cougars at New Mexico State Aggies

headlines.description: BYU 50, New Mexico St. 14

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Sam Ficken hit a 37-yard field goal in overtime, and Wisconsin's Kyle French attempt from 45 yards went wide left to seal Penn State's 24-21 win Saturday in an emotional season finale in Happy Valley.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn State prevails in OT; Ball sets TD record

headlines.description: Houston 40, Tulane 17

headlines.description: Fresno St. 48, Air Force 15

headlines.description: Middle Tennessee 24, Troy 21

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Bo Wallace threw for 294 yards and five touchdowns, Donte Moncrief caught three TD passes and Mississippi pulled away in the second half to beat Mississippi State 41-24 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ole Miss gets first Egg Bowl win since 2008
